{
  "_doc": "Adventures in the Forgotten Realms (AFR) Draft + Collector recipes. The `draft` block is the original collation-derived recipe from data/_collation-facts/afr.json (The Collation Project) and is kept verbatim. The `collector` block was added from Wizards' official 'Collecting Adventures in the Forgotten Realms' article (https://magic.wizards.com/en/news/feature/collecting-adventures-forgotten-realms-2021-06-29) plus its product-overview Collector Booster graphic. AFR (Jul 2021) is pre-Play-Booster, so there is intentionally NO play booster; Set Boosters are skipped per assignment. authoritative=true. Set composition: 101C / 80U / 60R / 20M, no double-faced cards. Sub-set codes: AFR = main set, AFC = AFR Commander (the extended-art Commander slot), TAFR = tokens. Collector Booster = 16 (15 cards + 1 foil double-sided token): 4 foil commons, 1 foil showcase/borderless common-or-uncommon, 2 foil showcase/borderless commons-or-uncommons (total 3 foil booster-fun low-rarity), 2 foil uncommons, 1 foil basic land, 1 extended-art rare/mythic (main set), 1 extended-art Commander rare/mythic, 1 foil rare/mythic, 1 non-foil showcase/borderless rare/mythic, 1 foil showcase/borderless/extended-art rare/mythic, 1 foil token. Article pool sizes used to DERIVE weights (exact percentages were not published): AFR extended-art '30 rares / 7 mythic rares' -> by count 30:7 = 81.1% rare / 18.9% mythic; AFR Commander extended-art '48 rares / 8 mythic rares' -> 48:8 = 85.7% rare / 14.3% mythic. Booster-fun rare/mythic treatments: 51 rulebook (monster-manual) rares, 5 borderless planeswalkers, 11 borderless Dragons, 9 module (borderless) lands. The article states a Foil Mythic Borderless Planeswalker appears in 4% of Collector Boosters; that 4% is placed in the final foil alt-frame slot. Approximations: rulebook / monster-manual frame and module-land treatments have no dedicated filter, so rulebook cards use showcase and module lands use borderless (+ non_basic_land where they are the chase land); borderless planeswalkers/Dragons use borderless; extended-art uses extended_art; full-art basic lands use basic_land. AUDIT 2026-06: borderless common outcome re-raritied to uncommon (AFR borderless C/U prints are 5 uncommons, zero commons — pool-verified).",
